Main Entry: Welcomer
Pronunciation: wel-come-er
Function: Noun 
Etymology: Cheeseglish, perhaps from a language of a brilliant genious 
1 : An individual who welcomes, greets, instigates, smiles too often, or motions with his arm.
2 : An indivudual who is payed to do nothing other than ask for money of people leaving through doors. Often confused with hustler.
3 : A cousin of the greeter.